<subSubSection id="C31F2DDDBF2CFFD27D35F857FE47D44A" pageId="27" pageNumber="438" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBA7E56BF2CFFD27D35F857FE47D44A" blockId="27.[813,1400,1921,2339]" lastBlockId="27.[198,1399,2351,2694]" pageId="27" pageNumber="438">
Has been considered conspecific with V. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF2CFFD27D34F868FCB5D517" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" box="[815,878,2040,2065]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Canis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="27" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="velox">velox</taxonomicName>
, based on morphometric similarities and protein-electrophoresis. Others have treated 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF2CFFD27DEAF7ADFBA7D558" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1888" box="[1009,1148,2109,2142]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="27" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">V. macrotis</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species based on multivariate morphometric data and more recent mitochondrial DNA analysis. Nominal subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF2CFFD27B09F728FBC2D5FA" authority="(Merriam, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="27" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">macrotis (Merriam, 1888)</taxonomicName>
from sout-western 
<collectingRegion id="49C1B0B4BF2CFFD27B22F74FFC59D425" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="27" pageNumber="438">California</collectingRegion>
is extinct. Seven extant subspecies are recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
